–1167","1108–1167":"1108–1167","1123–Female":"1123–Overleden","1144–1191":"1144–1191","1075–1134":"1075–1134","1084–1138":"1084–1138","environ 1167":"circa 1167","environ 1144":"circa 1144","1075":"1075","1084":"1084","1191":"1191","1138":"1138","1104":"1104","1134":"1134","1123":"1123","1167":"1167","1144":"1144","1108":"1108","environ 1138":"circa 1138","Crésecques, Mametz, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Mametz, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Frankrijk","Brugge, Flandre occidentale, Belgique":"Brugge, West-Vlaanderen, België","Creques, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Creques, Pas-de-Calais, Frankrijk","Mametz, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Mametz, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1108–environ 1167":"1108–about 1167","1104–1167":"1104–1167","1108–1167":"1108–1167","1123–Female":"1123–Deceased","1144–1191":"1144–1191","1075–1134":"1075–1134","1084–1138":"1084–1138","environ 1167":"about 1167","environ 1144":"about 1144","1075":"1075","1084":"1084","1191":"1191","1138":"1138","1104":"1104","1134":"1134","1123":"1123","1167":"1167","1144":"1144","1108":"1108","environ 1138":"about 1138","Crésecques, Mametz, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Mametz, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","Brugge, Flandre occidentale, Belgique":"Brugge, West Flanders, Belgium","Creques, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Creques, Pas-de-Calais, France","Mametz, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Mametz, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"DE","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert II DE CRESECQUE was born in 1108, his father, Robert Ier DE CRESECQUES, was 34 and his mother, Clémence DE RAMBURES, was 24. He married Briarde de Bruges about 1138, in Brugge, West Flanders, Belgium. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died about 1167, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1108–environ 1167":"1108–umbes 1167","1104–1167":"1104–1167","1108–1167":"1108–1167","1123–Female":"1123–Surnud","1144–1191":"1144–1191","1075–1134":"1075–1134","1084–1138":"1084–1138","environ 1167":"umbes 1167","environ 1144":"umbes 1144","1075":"1075","1084":"1084","1191":"1191","1138":"1138","1104":"1104","1134":"1134","1123":"1123","116